
[1]detection

   DETECTION, n. The act of detecting; discovery of a person or thing
   attempted to be concealed; as the detection of a thief or burglarian;
   the detection of fraud or forgery; the detection of artifice, device or
   a plot.

   2. Discovery of any thing before hidden, or unknown.

   The sea and rivers are instrumental to the detection of amber and other
   fossils, by washing away the earth that concealed them.
